        "text": "When you told Mrs. Bennet this morning that if you ever resolved upon quitting Netherfield you should be gone in five minutes, you meant it to be a sort of panegyric, of compliment to yourself\u2014and yet what is there so very laudable in a precipitance which must leave very necessary business undone, and can be of no real advantage to yourself or anyone else?\u201d \u201cNay,\u201d cried Bingley, \u201cthis is too much, to remember at night all the foolish things that were said in the morning.",
